I"<p>There are lot of useful plugins for Django CMS.
Well, this plugin let you use the images from a Facebook Album. Currently it supports fetching images from Photo Album of a Facebook Page.</p>

<p>All you need to do is to put Facebook Album URL, Access-token and the album name in the plugin fields and you will get a nice thumbnail in the intended place and once clicked big images will open in carousel effects. Sounds nice, take a look at the screen-shots below.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Entering the details in plugin form:</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="http://vinitcool76.github.io/images/admin.png" alt="Admin Page" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Thumbnail view of plugin:</li>
</ul>

<p>![Small View] (http://vinitcool76.github.io/imagessmallview.png)</p>

<ul>
  <li>Image slideshow in carousel</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="http://vinitcool76.github.io/images/bigview.png" alt="Carousel" /></p>

<p>#Installation</p>

<p>Installation is dead simple. First start your virtualenv</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ workon sample
(sample)$ pip install cmsplugin-fbalbum
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>You might need to do this if you are getting some sort of database error.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>python manage.py syncdb
python manage.py migrate
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>In case you face any problems, file issues and if you want to contribute take a look at the existing issues and send a pull request.</p>

